    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i know there are people, but they aren't the ones in my body. they aren't the ones feeling this every single second. it's not just being \"sad,\" it's the sheer exhaustion of existing in this much pain. sometimes it feels like there's a sense of mercy in the idea of just... stopping. like, if the pain was gone, everything would finally be at peace. wouldn't that just be a kindness?",
